## Overview

Implement the bind phase for the vgi_table_function DuckDB table function. The bind phase discovers the function's return schema and validates parameters.

## Function Signature

```sql
vgi_table_function(worker_path VARCHAR, function_name VARCHAR, args ANY[])
```

Or with named arguments:
```sql
vgi_table_function(
    worker VARCHAR,
    func VARCHAR,
    args ANY[] DEFAULT [],
    named_args MAP(VARCHAR, ANY) DEFAULT MAP {}
)
```

## Bind Phase Responsibilities

1. **Parse Input Parameters**:
   - Extract worker path (required)
   - Extract function name (required)
   - Extract positional args list (optional, default empty)
   - Extract named args map (optional, default empty)

2. **Attach to Catalog** (if not already attached):
   - Call catalog_attach to get attach_id
   - Cache attach_id for reuse

3. **Get Function Metadata**:
   - Call function_get with attach_id, schema, function_name
   - Retrieve VgiFunctionInfo with return_schema

4. **Convert Arrow Schema to DuckDB Types**:
   - Use ArrowSchemaWrapper or similar to convert Arrow types
   - Build vector of LogicalType for return columns
   - Build vector of string for column names

5. **Create Bind Data**:
   - Store worker_path, function_name, attach_id
   - Store parsed positional and named arguments
   - Store return schema information
   - Store cardinality estimate (if available)

## Implementation

### New Files:
- src/include/vgi_table_function.hpp
- src/vgi_table_function.cpp

### VgiTableFunctionBindData struct:

```cpp
struct VgiTableFunctionBindData : public TableFunctionData {
    // Worker identification
    std::string worker_path;
    std::vector<uint8_t> attach_id;

    // Function identification
    std::string schema_name;
    std::string function_name;

    // Arguments
    std::vector<Value> positional_args;
    case_insensitive_map_t<Value> named_args;

    // Schema information
    std::shared_ptr<arrow::Schema> arrow_schema;
    vector<LogicalType> return_types;
    vector<string> return_names;

    // Optimization hints
    idx_t cardinality_estimate;
    int32_t max_workers;

    // Projection pushdown
    vector<idx_t> projection_ids;
};
```

### VgiTableFunctionBind function:

```cpp
unique_ptr<FunctionData> VgiTableFunctionBind(
    ClientContext &context,
    TableFunctionBindInput &input,
    vector<LogicalType> &return_types,
    vector<string> &names) {

    // 1. Extract parameters
    auto worker_path = input.inputs[0].GetValue<string>();
    auto function_name = input.inputs[1].GetValue<string>();
    auto args_list = ListValue::GetChildren(input.inputs[2]);

    // 2. Attach to catalog
    auto attach_result = AttachToCatalog(worker_path, context);

    // 3. Get function info
    auto func_info = GetFunctionInfo(
        worker_path, attach_result.attach_id, 
        "main", function_name, context);

    // 4. Convert schema
    for (auto &field : func_info.return_schema->fields()) {
        return_types.push_back(ArrowToDuckDBType(field->type()));
        names.push_back(field->name());
    }

    // 5. Create bind data
    auto bind_data = make_uniq<VgiTableFunctionBindData>();
    bind_data->worker_path = worker_path;
    bind_data->attach_id = attach_result.attach_id;
    bind_data->function_name = function_name;
    bind_data->positional_args = args_list;
    bind_data->arrow_schema = func_info.return_schema;
    bind_data->return_types = return_types;
    bind_data->return_names = names;
    bind_data->cardinality_estimate = func_info.cardinality_estimate;

    return bind_data;
}
```

### Arrow Type Conversion

Use existing DuckDB Arrow integration or implement conversion:

```cpp
LogicalType ArrowToDuckDBType(const std::shared_ptr<arrow::DataType> &arrow_type) {
    switch (arrow_type->id()) {
        case arrow::Type::BOOL: return LogicalType::BOOLEAN;
        case arrow::Type::INT8: return LogicalType::TINYINT;
        case arrow::Type::INT16: return LogicalType::SMALLINT;
        case arrow::Type::INT32: return LogicalType::INTEGER;
        case arrow::Type::INT64: return LogicalType::BIGINT;
        case arrow::Type::FLOAT: return LogicalType::FLOAT;
        case arrow::Type::DOUBLE: return LogicalType::DOUBLE;
        case arrow::Type::STRING:
        case arrow::Type::LARGE_STRING: return LogicalType::VARCHAR;
        case arrow::Type::BINARY:
        case arrow::Type::LARGE_BINARY: return LogicalType::BLOB;
        case arrow::Type::DATE32:
        case arrow::Type::DATE64: return LogicalType::DATE;
        case arrow::Type::TIMESTAMP: return LogicalType::TIMESTAMP;
        case arrow::Type::LIST:
        case arrow::Type::LARGE_LIST: {
            auto list_type = std::static_pointer_cast<arrow::ListType>(arrow_type);
            return LogicalType::LIST(ArrowToDuckDBType(list_type->value_type()));
        }
        case arrow::Type::STRUCT: {
            // Convert struct fields recursively
            child_list_t<LogicalType> children;
            auto struct_type = std::static_pointer_cast<arrow::StructType>(arrow_type);
            for (auto &field : struct_type->fields()) {
                children.push_back({field->name(), ArrowToDuckDBType(field->type())});
            }
            return LogicalType::STRUCT(children);
        }
        // ... more types
        default:
            throw NotImplementedException("Arrow type not supported: %s", arrow_type->ToString());
    }
}
```

## Cardinality Estimation

```cpp
unique_ptr<NodeStatistics> VgiTableFunctionCardinality(
    ClientContext &context, const FunctionData *bind_data_p) {
    auto &bind_data = bind_data_p->Cast<VgiTableFunctionBindData>();
    if (bind_data.cardinality_estimate > 0) {
        return make_uniq<NodeStatistics>(bind_data.cardinality_estimate);
    }
    return nullptr;
}
