## Overview

Implement the init (global and local) and scan phases for the vgi_table_function. This handles starting the function invocation and streaming Arrow data back to DuckDB.

## Architecture

Following the DuckDB table function pattern:
1. **Global Init**: Set up shared state, start function invocation
2. **Local Init**: Per-thread state (for parallel execution)
3. **Scan Function**: Read Arrow batches, convert to DuckDB vectors

## Global Init Phase

### VgiTableFunctionGlobalState:

```cpp
struct VgiTableFunctionGlobalState : public GlobalTableFunctionState {
    // Stream from worker
    std::unique_ptr<FunctionInvokeStream> stream;

    // Current batch being processed
    std::shared_ptr<arrow::RecordBatch> current_batch;
    idx_t current_batch_offset;

    // Completion tracking
    std::atomic<bool> exhausted;

    // Thread safety
    std::mutex stream_lock;

    idx_t MaxThreads() const override {
        // Single-threaded for now; can expand for partitioned functions
        return 1;
    }
};
```

### VgiTableFunctionInitGlobal:

```cpp
unique_ptr<GlobalTableFunctionState> VgiTableFunctionInitGlobal(
    ClientContext &context,
    TableFunctionInitInput &input) {

    auto &bind_data = input.bind_data->Cast<VgiTableFunctionBindData>();
    auto state = make_uniq<VgiTableFunctionGlobalState>();

    // Apply projection pushdown if supported
    vector<idx_t> projection_ids;
    if (input.projection_ids) {
        projection_ids = *input.projection_ids;
    }

    // Start function invocation stream
    state->stream = make_uniq<FunctionInvokeStream>(
        bind_data.worker_path,
        bind_data.attach_id,
        bind_data.schema_name,
        bind_data.function_name,
        bind_data.positional_args,
        bind_data.named_args,
        projection_ids,
        context
    );

    state->exhausted = false;
    state->current_batch_offset = 0;

    return state;
}
```

## Local Init Phase

For single-threaded execution, local state is minimal:

```cpp
